00:35:25.289 --> 00:35:26.833
Are you the general overseer here?

00:35:26.916 --> 00:35:29.961
Yes, I'm the general over-- Overseer?

00:35:30.044 --> 00:35:32.672
I am frustrated because I am getting nowhere with this useless

00:35:32.755 --> 00:35:34.674
follower, so I am glad you are here.

00:35:34.757 --> 00:35:37.927
Let us walk over to that tranquil spot and discuss further.

00:35:38.010 --> 00:35:39.762
-That won't be… -Director, sir,

00:35:39.846 --> 00:35:41.139
What's going on here?

00:35:41.806 --> 00:35:44.559
Ji-hyo, she's from your agency, isn't she? Where's Mrs. Hong? I want you

00:35:44.642 --> 00:35:47.436
to get Mrs. Hong right now. She should really keep her actors on a leash.

00:35:47.520 --> 00:35:48.688
I won't stand for it!

00:35:48.771 --> 00:35:51.816
What's wrong? Has Seo-ri messed up or done something wrong already? If so, I'm

00:35:51.899 --> 00:35:57.196
sorry. I told Mrs. Hong not to impose her just because we're in the same agency.

00:35:58.322 --> 00:36:00.324
As the lead actress, I feel responsible.

00:36:01.909 --> 00:36:05.413
This is exactly the reason why I told you not to hire a veteran rookie, you

00:36:05.496 --> 00:36:07.373
stupid idiot! Did you pick her?

00:36:07.456 --> 00:36:10.418
She's a forced hire? That sure explains a lot.

00:36:11.335 --> 00:36:14.714
Are these people really publicly shaming me right here, in front of

00:36:14.797 --> 00:36:15.798
my face?

00:36:18.217 --> 00:36:20.678
Okay, since Ji-hyo is being so apologetic, I'll let it slide this

00:36:20.761 --> 00:36:24.515
time, but no second chance. You should bow down and thank Ji-Hyo!

00:36:24.599 --> 00:36:25.600
What was that?

00:36:25.683 --> 00:36:29.228
No. Please, Director, calm down, there's no need for that. Since everyone

00:36:29.312 --> 00:36:32.857
is working so hard, I'll buy everyone here a round of iced coffee

00:36:32.940 --> 00:36:36.485
to officially celebrate the start of Season Two, okay? Come on, everyone,

00:36:36.569 --> 00:36:39.071
-let's go! No way. No, don't worry about -Just a second, overseer!

00:36:39.155 --> 00:36:41.991
Seo-ri, let's go. What's in store for this season? Do you know if we'll be

00:36:42.074 --> 00:36:43.743
-Overseer? -Thank you.

00:36:43.826 --> 00:36:45.745
-Overseer? -Able to get all the scripts?

00:36:45.828 --> 00:36:48.539
Uh, I'm not sure yet, we have a meeting next week. I'll know more then.

00:36:48.623 --> 00:36:50.291
Are you going to the coffee truck?

00:36:50.374 --> 00:36:51.792
I need to eat something too.

00:36:53.961 --> 00:36:55.755
Cut! Okay, next scene!

00:37:00.259 --> 00:37:01.344
Thank you very much.

00:37:03.387 --> 00:37:06.891
That vixen is marking this place as her territory and trying to show me

00:37:06.974 --> 00:37:10.561
who's boss. How utterly dispicable. I must quickly establish my name in

00:37:10.645 --> 00:37:12.104
this world.

00:37:14.815 --> 00:37:16.692
Ms. Shin! Thank you for the latte.

00:37:16.776 --> 00:37:18.611
Thank you, Lots of luck, Seo-ri!

00:37:18.694 --> 00:37:19.862
Thanks for the coffee.

00:37:19.946 --> 00:37:21.030
Thank you!

00:37:21.113 --> 00:37:22.740
-Thanks. -Thank you very much.

00:37:22.823 --> 00:37:23.950
Thanks for the coffee.

00:37:24.784 --> 00:37:28.162
Huh? Why are they suddenly all being nice to me?

00:37:34.210 --> 00:37:35.962
This is a pretty incredible set-up.

00:37:36.671 --> 00:37:39.215
Your call cannot be connected and is being forwarded to a voicemail

00:37:39.298 --> 00:37:41.676
-service… -That jerk actually blocked me.

00:37:42.468 --> 00:37:43.719
What a little asshole.

00:37:47.181 --> 00:37:49.809
Go get me an iced Americano with lots of ice, okay?

00:37:49.892 --> 00:37:50.935
Sure.

00:37:51.018 --> 00:37:54.689
Yeah, of course, understood. They said the delivery will take a while because

00:37:54.772 --> 00:37:55.690
of the lunch rush.

00:37:56.983 --> 00:37:58.693
You mean those aren't the coffees we ordered?

00:37:58.776 --> 00:38:01.654
What? Hang on… Who ordered a coffee truck? Okay, then, I'll call and cancel

00:38:01.737 --> 00:38:04.198
our order right now. Hey!

00:38:04.282 --> 00:38:05.241
Huh?

00:38:05.324 --> 00:38:09.036
The lead hasn't even gotten one yet. Which jerk ordered that coffee truck?

00:38:09.578 --> 00:38:12.707
Hey, wait a second, let me see, let me see. "Brought to you by

00:38:12.790 --> 00:38:15.793
acting legend, Ms. Shin Seo-ri?" Look at this!

00:38:17.920 --> 00:38:20.673
So, Shin Seo-ri's the one who ordered this whole thing?

00:38:20.756 --> 00:38:23.259
BROUGHT TO YOU BY THE ACTING VIRTUOSO, SHIN SEO-RI

00:38:28.723 --> 00:38:29.849
This is me, everyone.

00:38:31.100 --> 00:38:32.518
Would you look this way, please?

00:38:32.601 --> 00:38:34.478
You're so pretty. I'm a fan of yours.

00:38:38.899 --> 00:38:41.319
-Do you mind taking a picture with me? -Uh-huh.

00:38:41.402 --> 00:38:42.778
One, two, three.

00:38:45.031 --> 00:38:45.865
Oh, thank you.

00:38:45.948 --> 00:38:47.700
Thank you again for the iced coffee, Seo-ri.

00:38:47.783 --> 00:38:50.369
-That was really nice of you. -Thank you very much.

00:38:50.453 --> 00:38:52.038
Thank you, everyone, thank you.

00:38:52.913 --> 00:38:55.750
I do not think I have ever had so many people thank me for something in

00:38:55.833 --> 00:38:57.251
my entire life. It is definitely

00:38:57.335 --> 00:39:00.087
-better than being treated like common -Would you please look over here?

00:39:00.171 --> 00:39:02.298
-Dirt. -Seo-ri, you're so pretty!

00:39:03.174 --> 00:39:05.551
I am Shin Seo-ri. I am Shin Seo-ri.

00:39:08.012 --> 00:39:09.263
Okay, now smile.

00:39:12.224 --> 00:39:13.976
So, what do you think, Shin Seo-ri?

00:39:16.437 --> 00:39:18.814
Is a wave of gratitude finally washing over you?

00:39:18.898 --> 00:39:19.732
Cha Se-gye?

00:39:20.983 --> 00:39:22.401
Don't say my name out loud.

00:39:22.485 --> 00:39:26.113
Wait… Do you mean you did all this, Cha Se-gye?

00:39:26.197 --> 00:39:28.115
I just told you not to say my name out loud! Jeez!

00:39:28.199 --> 00:39:29.158
You wretched scoundrel.

00:39:29.241 --> 00:39:32.161
Mrs. Hong, you bundled Shin Seo-ri in with me as a package deal without

00:39:32.244 --> 00:39:34.914
asking me, and now you order a coffee truck for her?

00:39:34.997 --> 00:39:37.750
Please, have you ever seen me waste money on things like that? There's a

00:39:37.833 --> 00:39:40.669
hierarchy to these things. Why would I get her a coffee truck before I get

00:39:40.753 --> 00:39:42.380
-one for you? -I…

00:39:42.880 --> 00:39:46.717
Well, I… so, it… it wasn't you who ordered it? So, who the hell is throwing

00:39:46.801 --> 00:39:49.637
money around like that?

00:39:50.262 --> 00:39:52.681
Maybe it's one of her fans who sent it to her.

00:39:52.765 --> 00:39:54.725
Oh, come on, she doesn't have any.

00:40:00.773 --> 00:40:01.690
For goodness sake…

00:40:05.277 --> 00:40:09.156
What are you up to? What are you scheming that you have to resort to bribery?

00:40:10.449 --> 00:40:13.369
I guess bribery's the right word, since I do have an ulterior motive.

00:40:13.452 --> 00:40:14.453
What's that?

00:40:15.079 --> 00:40:21.836
So you are finally showing your true colors. So, tell me your motive.

00:40:28.050 --> 00:40:30.136
As of today, this will be my only target.

00:40:31.846 --> 00:40:34.682
You want my heart? What will you do with my heart?

00:40:34.765 --> 00:40:36.684
I've made a plan to steal it from you.

00:40:38.853 --> 00:40:41.647
You said you don't feel anything. That you felt more when you hugged that

00:40:41.730 --> 00:40:44.733
stray mutt. You have no idea how angry that made me, I couldn't fall asleep for

00:40:44.817 --> 00:40:45.651
days.

00:40:45.734 --> 00:40:48.779
Whether you sleep or do handstands, I am not concerned by that.

00:40:48.863 --> 00:40:51.907
You're acting tough again. The thing is, I realized that I'd overlooked

00:40:51.991 --> 00:40:52.992
something.

00:40:53.951 --> 00:40:54.785
And what was it?

00:40:54.869 --> 00:40:57.329
That you, Shin Seo-ri, are not pure and innocent.

00:40:58.873 --> 00:41:01.375
So, what you are saying is that I am dirty and sleazy?

00:41:01.459 --> 00:41:04.837
No, just a damn good liar, and you would do almost anything to get what

00:41:04.920 --> 00:41:07.381
you want. The truth is, you're a dangerous woman.

00:41:09.592 --> 00:41:13.262
Is he saying that he has decided to cancel our contract?

00:41:13.762 --> 00:41:17.016
But, the thing is, I can't give up because I was never taught to lose.

00:41:17.099 --> 00:41:19.768
Doesn't matter 'cause I know I'm gonna win this time.

00:41:21.020 --> 00:41:23.397
Or is he saying… that he wants to fight?

00:41:25.316 --> 00:41:26.150
Is this revenge?

00:41:26.233 --> 00:41:30.988
No, I'm surrendering. People say that, in love and war, losing is winning.

00:41:34.283 --> 00:41:36.535
What is this? He's attacking me with his eyes.

00:41:36.619 --> 00:41:39.914
I know I overreacted. I didn't even try to impress you with any

00:41:39.997 --> 00:41:43.584
grand gestures. So, I suggest that we forget everything that's happened

00:41:43.667 --> 00:41:46.170
so far, and start over.

00:41:46.670 --> 00:41:50.049
What is this eccentricity? The earnestness of his gaze is at odds

00:41:50.132 --> 00:41:54.470
with his foolish core. Could it be…

00:41:56.514 --> 00:42:00.267
Tell me, do you truly yearn for my affection?

00:42:01.018 --> 00:42:01.977
I do yearn for you.

00:42:08.776 --> 00:42:12.363
What is this fool thinking? Why is he rushing headstrong so recklessly?

00:42:23.874 --> 00:42:27.545
Okay, I know you're a woman, so accepting this right away would hurt your

00:42:27.628 --> 00:42:31.882
pride, is that it? I can grant you a day or two to save face.

00:42:31.966 --> 00:42:34.677
No need. I will give you an answer right now.

00:42:36.845 --> 00:42:40.140
It has been the case all along, and will remain so. Cha Se-gye, listen

00:42:40.224 --> 00:42:43.936
carefully. I do not yearn for you, and I will never, for all eternity,

00:42:44.019 --> 00:42:45.771
yearn for you.

00:43:01.662 --> 00:43:04.707
Oh, what a devilish scoundrel. Launching a surprise attack in close

00:43:04.790 --> 00:43:05.624
quarters.

00:43:07.293 --> 00:43:09.962
I am a Buddhist nun. A nun with long hair.

00:43:25.269 --> 00:43:28.647
Hey, Shin Seo-ri. Take this, the smell is giving me a headache.

00:43:28.731 --> 00:43:29.898
What…

00:43:32.401 --> 00:43:35.988
-You had brought me flowers? -Don't piss me off by rubbing it in, okay?

00:43:47.124 --> 00:43:48.000
What is going on?

00:43:51.503 --> 00:43:56.592
Woah, that's a sports car! Shin Seo-ri actually has a real boyfriend?

00:44:10.939 --> 00:44:14.777
I can't believe she turned me down! Not just once. She turned me down twice!

00:44:20.032 --> 00:44:22.117
INCOMING CALL DEPARTMENT HEAD SON JAE-HAN

00:44:22.201 --> 00:44:23.410
DEPARTMENT HEAD SON JAE-HAN

00:44:23.494 --> 00:44:25.245
Mr. Cha, are you on your way? You have dinner at the chairman's mansion

00:44:25.329 --> 00:44:27.122
tonight. I wanted to make sure you didn't…

00:44:27.206 --> 00:44:29.792
Do you have any idea what kind of humiliation I've just been through

00:44:29.875 --> 00:44:30.709
because of you?

00:44:31.293 --> 00:44:32.878
I don't. I'm sorry, what did I do…

00:44:32.961 --> 00:44:36.382
Why the hell did I ask a bachelor, who lives with a cat, for advice?

00:44:53.565 --> 00:44:54.400
Shit…

00:44:55.234 --> 00:44:59.238
I'm really sorry. Are you alright? Oh, it's you again.

00:45:00.114 --> 00:45:00.948
Sorry?

00:45:01.740 --> 00:45:05.035
At the shop earlier… Don't you remember?

00:45:05.577 --> 00:45:07.996
Shop? Which shop? Have we met?

00:45:08.080 --> 00:45:11.834
Yes, I was at the tailor's shop and I accidentally spilled coffee on you.

00:45:11.917 --> 00:45:15.295
Now, I remember… You're quite accident-prone, aren't you?

00:45:16.797 --> 00:45:19.925
I don't usually have a forgettable face, from what I've heard.

00:45:22.469 --> 00:45:25.639
Please don't forget me this time and call me. The after effects of a car

00:45:25.723 --> 00:45:26.849
accident can be awful.

00:45:31.895 --> 00:45:32.730
"Trinice?"

00:45:32.813 --> 00:45:35.607
It's my company. As you can see, I too, can pay for my own suits and car

00:45:35.691 --> 00:45:38.569
repairs. So, don't hesitate to send me your medical bill.

00:45:52.708 --> 00:45:56.086
It's the face-off of a tiger and a dragon. Of a spear and a shield,

00:45:56.170 --> 00:45:58.213
a battle between two proud geniuses.

00:45:58.714 --> 00:46:01.467
I thought you told me not to go on blind dates. Well, it doesn't matter

00:46:01.550 --> 00:46:05.512
either way because, in that field, I've already struck out.

00:46:05.596 --> 00:46:08.140
Well, maybe you've struck out domestically, but you look abroad,

00:46:08.223 --> 00:46:10.100
plenty of women to choose from.

00:46:10.184 --> 00:46:12.811
If your opponent is being unreasonable, be the same.

00:46:12.895 --> 00:46:15.272
Grandfather, a cracked plate will always be a cracked plate, no

00:46:15.355 --> 00:46:16.857
matter what country you're in.

00:46:16.940 --> 00:46:19.234
Stop being stupid and set up a meeting for this week. I really

00:46:19.318 --> 00:46:21.445
don't care if she can't speak Korean well.

00:46:22.488 --> 00:46:25.866
Draw an absurd conclusion by using false logic and distortion.

00:46:27.993 --> 00:46:29.703
I really don't have time for this.

00:46:35.959 --> 00:46:38.378
What, exactly, are you trying to pull right now?

00:46:41.340 --> 00:46:42.966
To think that you almost had me.

00:46:45.135 --> 00:46:47.471
Okay, you caught me. You're so terrible at blind dates that I

00:46:47.554 --> 00:46:50.432
thought it would be much easier for me to organize a natural encounter with

00:46:50.516 --> 00:46:54.019
someone you could like. Why would that be so bad?

00:46:54.102 --> 00:46:57.189
So you know about natural encounters. Either way, if she's willing to go along

00:46:57.272 --> 00:47:00.943
with such a ridiculous stunt, I can tell she's stupid or naive.

00:47:01.026 --> 00:47:03.570
She's an intelligent young lady who doesn't fall short of you in

00:47:03.654 --> 00:47:05.364
any way. That's what made me change my mind.

00:47:05.447 --> 00:47:08.408
So, you've been on a blind date with her. Well, if you like her, why don't you

00:47:08.492 --> 00:47:10.619
-marry her yourself. -How dare you talk to me that way!

00:47:10.702 --> 00:47:13.497
When your opponent is winning, launch personal attacks. It's the best way

00:47:13.580 --> 00:47:14.832
to win your battle.

00:47:16.250 --> 00:47:17.084
K.O.

00:47:35.853 --> 00:47:36.812
I do yearn for you.

00:47:41.358 --> 00:47:42.192
Ugh!

00:47:49.533 --> 00:47:52.995
You think some cliché bouquet of flowers is going to make me budge an

00:47:53.078 --> 00:47:56.832
inch? Safety and security come first… and also come second. In this life, I

00:47:56.915 --> 00:48:03.839
will make sure to guard my heart from pain… and live to be very old.

00:48:18.687 --> 00:48:19.646
Kang clan, Dan-sim.

00:48:23.317 --> 00:48:25.193
Your Royal Highness, why are you here?

00:48:25.277 --> 00:48:28.655
Well, these are my quarters. And what are you doing here?

00:48:29.698 --> 00:48:30.824
I… I was…

00:48:40.584 --> 00:48:44.171
What are you burying? Is it a norigae that you stole perchance?

00:48:46.423 --> 00:48:50.677
I haven't stolen anything, sir. Do you think I look like a thief?

00:48:51.678 --> 00:48:55.265
Ah, yes, there is that look. No need to look like a sad puppy caught in

00:48:55.349 --> 00:48:58.185
the rain, since being lively is more like you.

00:48:59.686 --> 00:49:03.231
Speaking of which, where is that silly puppy hiding?

00:49:07.611 --> 00:49:09.404
You didn't chase him away, did you?

00:49:18.664 --> 00:49:21.124
Has it… Has it died?

00:49:25.545 --> 00:49:26.380
It has died…

00:49:29.841 --> 00:49:31.468
and I was the one who killed it.

00:49:35.180 --> 00:49:38.850
I doubt that is true. If you truly did kill it, you would not be making a

00:49:38.934 --> 00:49:41.269
grave for it with such a devastated face.

00:49:51.989 --> 00:49:55.075
I think you and I should pray at least for this poor nameless

00:49:55.158 --> 00:49:59.037
puppy's soul. For his rebirth in the Land of Bliss.

00:50:02.791 --> 00:50:08.088
I pray… that you be reborn as a human, and that you live a very long life.

00:50:15.887 --> 00:50:17.389
May you live a very long life.

00:51:21.244 --> 00:51:23.330
Why would he give me something like this?

00:51:26.249 --> 00:51:29.002
I can't just throw away something that is so pretty.

00:51:29.086 --> 00:51:31.463
Why would you throw away a bouquet of flowers?

00:51:31.546 --> 00:51:34.591
Did someone confess their feelings, and you didn't like it? Was it Unit 204?

00:51:34.674 --> 00:51:37.677
Just be quiet. Stop talking and quickly finish your laundry.

00:51:38.720 --> 00:51:39.554
Okay, fine.

00:51:43.016 --> 00:51:46.436
Did you watch Kingdom of Women the other day? They're finally airing

00:51:46.520 --> 00:51:47.354
season Two!

00:51:47.437 --> 00:51:51.441
Yoon Ji-hyo's even prettier than before. She must spend a fortune on treatments.

00:51:51.525 --> 00:51:55.612
That vixen's dewy glow is just the result of her caked-on powder white make-up.

00:51:56.154 --> 00:51:58.615
Why is she butting in after telling us to be quiet?

00:51:58.698 --> 00:52:01.535
She's just dissing her because she's jealous. It's not like she's seen her

00:52:01.618 --> 00:52:04.162
-in person. -Of course I have. I saw her yesterday.

00:52:04.246 --> 00:52:05.080
Oh, yeah? Where?

00:52:05.914 --> 00:52:08.625
Maybe it was at one of her part-time jobs. I hear Roof unit's a wannabe

00:52:08.708 --> 00:52:09.668
actress.

00:52:09.751 --> 00:52:11.044
Get outta here, that's crazy.

00:52:11.128 --> 00:52:12.337
No, it's true, she works on set.

00:52:12.420 --> 00:52:14.673
I don't believe it. It's not like anyone can be an actress.

00:52:14.756 --> 00:52:15.590
Ungrateful brats!

00:52:15.674 --> 00:52:19.052
How can they be so mean when I let them dry their laundry up here?

00:52:22.848 --> 00:52:25.809
It is like I always say: No good deed ever goes unpunished.

00:52:33.441 --> 00:52:36.403
I'm sending you the schedule for the Jeju Island shoot coming up in two days,

00:52:36.486 --> 00:52:39.322
so pack your bags. Since Ji-hyo's on vacation, you can use her van and her

00:52:39.406 --> 00:52:41.741
manager for now. The van will pick you up.

00:52:41.825 --> 00:52:44.244
No thanks. I refuse to use anything that belongs to that vixen.

00:52:44.327 --> 00:52:48.081
I will select someone from my own acquaintances, so no need to worry.

00:52:54.171 --> 00:52:55.797
You haven't slept at all lately?

00:52:55.881 --> 00:52:58.717
Every time I try to sleep, the things that piss me off pop back into my

00:52:58.800 --> 00:52:59.634
head.

00:52:59.718 --> 00:53:02.053
Everyone plays back what happened to them when they're in bed. Just try to

00:53:02.137 --> 00:53:03.430
stop thinking, or try medication.

00:53:03.513 --> 00:53:06.641
And how do I stop thinking? I've never been humiliated in my life.

00:53:06.725 --> 00:53:09.895
I saw. Everyone is blasting you for being a heartless corporate raider.

00:53:09.978 --> 00:53:13.190
I just can't let things stand like this. It's embarrasing.

00:53:15.358 --> 00:53:16.484
How can I get revenge?

00:53:17.485 --> 00:53:21.114
What do you mean by revenge? Every public opinion gets replaced by a new

00:53:21.198 --> 00:53:24.367
public opinion. Just wait quietly. In time, it will go away.

00:53:24.868 --> 00:53:26.077
Replaced?

00:53:28.496 --> 00:53:32.250
Yeah. Replace. I like that. Thanks for today's consult. You're turning into

00:53:32.334 --> 00:53:34.211
a great doctor.

00:53:37.505 --> 00:53:39.049
Hey, take your meds, okay?

00:53:42.510 --> 00:53:45.597
Sorry, Ms. Kim, would you mind giving these meds to Mr. Cha Se-gye?

00:53:45.680 --> 00:53:47.641
No, I'll give them to him right now.

00:53:49.893 --> 00:53:53.480
Oh, Mr. Son, call my grandfather now. Tell him I've agreed to go on his

00:53:53.563 --> 00:53:54.898
blind date this week.

00:53:55.398 --> 00:53:57.651
Mr. Cha, your medication is ready for pickup.

00:54:00.278 --> 00:54:02.405
Listen, stop talking and just do as I say.

00:54:03.031 --> 00:54:04.407
HANBIT MENTAL HEALTH CLINIC

00:54:07.244 --> 00:54:09.412
DELIVERY COMPLETE

00:54:17.671 --> 00:54:21.174
"It is formed as an autonomous organization to which all citizens have

00:54:21.258 --> 00:54:24.010
delegated a self-governing authority."

00:54:24.511 --> 00:54:25.720
Is it good?

00:54:25.804 --> 00:54:30.100
Are you crazy? You should make noise instead of creeping around like a ghost.

00:54:38.316 --> 00:54:41.778
He may be a little on the scrawny side, but he can sustain himself on

00:54:41.861 --> 00:54:46.616
instant noodles and is exceedingly frugal. I can tell he is resourceful.

00:54:50.537 --> 00:54:51.371
What's wrong?

00:54:52.163 --> 00:54:55.542
Moreover, no matter how harshly I treat him, he always fights back.

00:54:55.625 --> 00:54:58.253
That says he has far more grit than meets the eye.

00:55:00.463 --> 00:55:03.341
So, will you be my… attendant?

00:55:03.425 --> 00:55:04.926
What are you talking about?

00:55:05.010 --> 00:55:08.346
What I mean is, I have chosen you to serve as my travel attendant.

00:55:08.430 --> 00:55:10.348
Travel… attendant? What's that?

00:55:10.432 --> 00:55:13.143
It is a person who will attend to my needs during my road travels.

00:55:13.226 --> 00:55:15.562
You do not know what a road attendant is? You do not know what a road attendant is?

00:55:15.645 --> 00:55:16.479
Road attendant…

00:55:21.651 --> 00:55:22.610
Oh, a road manager?

00:55:25.572 --> 00:55:28.616
You think I survived this long, busting my ass doing part-time jobs, day

00:55:28.700 --> 00:55:31.411
and night, just to end up as your chauffeur? I'll have you know,

00:55:31.494 --> 00:55:32.912
I actually have a bachelor's degree!

00:55:32.996 --> 00:55:36.166
So, you are educated. Wonderful. That is even better for this position. I have

00:55:36.249 --> 00:55:38.710
very high standards when selecting my underlings, yet after much

00:55:38.793 --> 00:55:41.046
consideration, I know no one better than you.

00:55:42.922 --> 00:55:45.383
Are you listening to me at all? It doesn't matter how desperate I

00:55:45.467 --> 00:55:47.969
am for money, I'd have to be nuts to work for you.

00:55:48.678 --> 00:55:51.848
How much would you be satisfied with? I will gladly meet your demands.

00:55:51.931 --> 00:55:54.184
Meet my demands? What d'you mean, you live on the roof!

00:55:54.267 --> 00:55:59.064
Three times your lowest current rate. Would triple pay be satisfactory?

00:56:01.983 --> 00:56:05.362
You think you can buy me with your money? I won't do it, I tell ya!

00:56:06.654 --> 00:56:10.367
I'm so royally screwed. I hate it that I'm so weak. But how could I say no

00:56:10.450 --> 00:56:13.286
when she offered to pay me triple?

00:56:13.787 --> 00:56:15.955
What are you doing? Get a move on it.

00:56:18.041 --> 00:56:21.503
Have you been to Jeju Island? Why are you all dressed up? And what's with those

00:56:21.586 --> 00:56:22.879
weird glasses you're wearing?

00:56:22.962 --> 00:56:26.591
As a celebrity, I must stay vigilant at all times, and ensure I look the

00:56:26.674 --> 00:56:30.345
part for my fans. Why are there no reporters here yet?

00:56:30.970 --> 00:56:33.640
Yeah, sure, I get it. Today, I saw online that the boss of the company

00:56:33.723 --> 00:56:36.226
you're shooting the ad for, is being accused of risk retention and

00:56:36.309 --> 00:56:40.230
perverse incentives. Doesn't that bother you at all?

00:56:40.313 --> 00:56:42.816
Why should I be concerned as long as I get paid?

00:56:43.608 --> 00:56:46.319
Okay. Like-minded people stay together, I guess.

00:56:50.281 --> 00:56:53.952
I'm not sure your presence is needed for the photoshoot of this campaign.

00:56:54.661 --> 00:56:57.497
This ad campaign is the most important part of our marketing

00:56:57.580 --> 00:57:01.000
strategy. As the client, I should be there to oversee it personally.

00:57:03.253 --> 00:57:06.840
I was planning on using some of my saved-up vacation days on this trip.

00:57:09.342 --> 00:57:13.179
Welcome aboard. We hope you have a pleasant flight. Welcome aboard.

00:57:13.263 --> 00:57:14.973
I can't wait til we get there!

00:57:15.515 --> 00:57:18.309
The things you see when you live long enough. I never would have thought I

00:57:18.393 --> 00:57:20.645
would fly through the sky without being dead.

00:57:22.814 --> 00:57:23.648
These.

00:57:25.942 --> 00:57:29.404
These are very comfortable seats. I can stretch my legs and lie down.

00:57:31.030 --> 00:57:33.533
Why did you rush off like that? I told you to wait for us to board

00:57:33.616 --> 00:57:34.451
together.

00:57:34.534 --> 00:57:37.871
You were taking too long. I secured good seats for us. Now, sit down.

00:57:37.954 --> 00:57:40.790
Wait… These aren't our seats! Come on, get up, quick!

00:57:41.374 --> 00:57:43.960
These are not our seats? Then where are our seats?

00:57:44.043 --> 00:57:45.795
Come on, get up. These aren't ours.

00:57:48.256 --> 00:57:51.926
Ladies and gentlemen. Welcome aboard our flight today. Please place

00:57:52.010 --> 00:57:54.971
-your personal items above in the bin -Because that section is business class,

00:57:55.054 --> 00:57:55.889
directly over your seat. We have a

00:57:55.972 --> 00:57:58.600
-full flight, so your cooperation is -and this is economy. If you like

00:57:58.683 --> 00:57:59.684
kindly appreciated. Small lightweight

00:57:59.767 --> 00:58:02.479
-items can be placed directly under -those seats so much, you should've

00:58:02.562 --> 00:58:03.521
the seat in front of you. Please turn

00:58:03.605 --> 00:58:05.565
-your phones to airplane mode or off -paid for them.

00:58:05.648 --> 00:58:07.317
Before our departure. If you need

00:58:07.400 --> 00:58:10.069
-any assistance, please press the call -You know, I wanted to ask you

00:58:10.153 --> 00:58:11.196
button directly over your head.

00:58:11.279 --> 00:58:14.240
These wretched people. They should have signs with "Pauper Section," "Peasant"

00:58:14.324 --> 00:58:15.783
and "Noblemen." Then I would have understood how this was organized.

00:58:15.867 --> 00:58:18.036
-Just before we take off, we'll conduct -Something ever since the first time

00:58:18.119 --> 00:58:19.996
our safety demostration to ensure you

00:58:20.079 --> 00:58:22.123
-feel properly prepared for a safe flight -we talked together. Did you finish every

00:58:22.207 --> 00:58:23.875
today. Your safety and experience

00:58:23.958 --> 00:58:24.792
is our top priority.

00:58:24.876 --> 00:58:25.710
Your vocabulary seems kind of archaic.

00:58:25.793 --> 00:58:26.669
Level in school?

00:58:27.212 --> 00:58:31.341
I know the language of the Continent. I have mastered the Elementary Learning.

00:58:32.050 --> 00:58:33.968
Okay, this should be fun.

00:58:45.605 --> 00:58:47.899
Mr. Cha, your insomnia issue is due to all your work, right?

00:58:47.982 --> 00:58:50.610
There's been no change to your personal life?

00:58:51.110 --> 00:58:54.572
Why? Did my grandfather call you in again to interrogate you?

00:58:54.656 --> 00:58:57.367
No. Of course not. Nothing like that happened at all.

00:58:57.450 --> 00:59:01.329
Well, he won't be bothering you anymore now that I'm going to do as he says.

00:59:01.412 --> 00:59:05.291
Why did you change your mind about this? I thought you were too busy with work?

00:59:05.375 --> 00:59:08.670
Well, it works out for me too. It's a win-win situation. Isn't it… getting too

00:59:08.753 --> 00:59:12.090
hot in here? Is it just me?

00:59:20.139 --> 00:59:20.974
I'll be right back.

00:59:21.057 --> 00:59:25.228
Of course, sir. Excuse me. Could he get a glass of cold water, please?

00:59:25.311 --> 00:59:26.354
Yes, of course.

00:59:35.530 --> 00:59:38.741
Would you please sit still for five minutes? The people in front are staring.

00:59:38.825 --> 00:59:41.286
I feel as though I have paid good money to be tortured. Even knee

00:59:41.369 --> 00:59:43.204
crushing would be better.

00:59:43.288 --> 00:59:46.541
Why? Do you always fly business class then? Just hang on for a little

00:59:46.624 --> 00:59:48.835
while longer. I'm going to use the restroom.

00:59:51.379 --> 00:59:53.506
Watch out, watch out, watch out, you wretch.

00:59:53.590 --> 00:59:55.174
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

00:59:56.134 --> 00:59:59.596
I was so excited to be flying through the sky. I never thought I would be

00:59:59.679 --> 01:00:02.974
attached and confined. I'm suffocating.

01:00:06.436 --> 01:00:08.896
May we have your attention, please? We have a medical emergency.

01:00:08.980 --> 01:00:11.482
If there's a medical professional on board, please notify a flight

01:00:11.566 --> 01:00:13.735
attendant. Thank you. May we have your attention, please?

01:00:13.818 --> 01:00:14.986
Oh, no, that's terrible.

01:00:15.069 --> 01:00:17.822
Excuse me, is there a doctor or a nurse on board? Is there a doctor or a

01:00:17.905 --> 01:00:20.241
-nurse on board? -Is there a doctor or a nurse on board?

01:00:20.325 --> 01:00:21.784
Is there a doctor or a nurse on board?

01:00:21.868 --> 01:00:23.161
Does anyone have medical training?

01:00:23.244 --> 01:00:24.245
We're looking for a doctor.

01:00:24.329 --> 01:00:25.872
Is there a doctor on board?

01:00:25.955 --> 01:00:27.665
Do we know what's happening?

01:00:27.749 --> 01:00:28.750
A doctor?

01:00:28.833 --> 01:00:32.795
Thank you very much for coming forward. We were so worried. It's such a relief

01:00:32.879 --> 01:00:35.048
to have a doctor on the plane.

01:00:35.548 --> 01:00:38.760
You said this person is on the verge of death. It is a human duty to save a

01:00:38.843 --> 01:00:39.969
life, even an enemy's.

01:00:40.595 --> 01:00:41.846
Do you practice Korean medicine?

01:00:41.929 --> 01:00:43.723
I am well known for my healing hands.

01:00:43.806 --> 01:00:46.768
When I was an apprentice court lady, the palace nurses would ask me to

01:00:46.851 --> 01:00:49.729
prick their fingers when they suffered from indigestion.

01:00:50.480 --> 01:00:52.940
Here he is. I've found a doctor.

01:00:55.318 --> 01:00:57.070
-Cha Se-gye? -Is he okay?

01:00:57.570 --> 01:01:00.281
Come on, Cha Se-gye, why are you on the floor like this?

01:01:00.365 --> 01:01:02.617
Do you know him? Oh, that's a good thing.

01:01:02.700 --> 01:01:04.911
This cannot be fixed by pricking his finger.

01:01:05.411 --> 01:01:07.789
Cha Se-gye, breathe. Come on, Cha Se-gye!

01:01:07.872 --> 01:01:09.832
Wait, what are you doing? You need to start CPR.

01:01:09.916 --> 01:01:11.584
What are you talking about?

01:01:13.127 --> 01:01:18.800
Oh, no. Ch-Cha Se-gye! Come on, Cha Se-gye! Breathe!

01:01:23.179 --> 01:01:24.722
-Oh, no! -Ladies and gentlemen,

01:01:24.806 --> 01:01:27.225
-we are experiencing some turbulence. -Hey, what are you doing? Hurry!

01:01:27.308 --> 01:01:30.019
Please return to your seats and fasten your seat belts.

01:01:30.103 --> 01:01:31.979
Ladies and gentlemen, we are experiencing

01:01:32.063 --> 01:01:33.981
-some turbulence. Please return to -Oh, my god!

01:01:34.065 --> 01:01:36.025
-Your seat and fasten your seat belt. -Does it help?

01:01:36.109 --> 01:01:37.735
Why did you do that to him?

01:01:37.819 --> 01:01:41.572
Cha Se-gye! Cha Se-gye, wake up, wake up! Wake up, wake up! Cha Se-gye! Cha…

01:01:41.656 --> 01:01:43.199
Cha Se-gye!

01:01:57.755 --> 01:02:00.508
Cha Se-gye, have you finally come to?

01:02:03.219 --> 01:02:05.888
Oh, I thought you were going to die, Cha Se-gye!

01:02:08.182 --> 01:02:09.016
You…

01:02:11.185 --> 01:02:12.019
Toxin…

01:02:12.103 --> 01:02:15.732
What? Toxin? Do you need herbal medicine? I can't hear you, what you're saying!

01:02:15.815 --> 01:02:16.816
Come on!

01:02:18.025 --> 01:02:18.860
Like poison.

01:02:19.360 --> 01:02:20.236
Poison?

01:02:27.243 --> 01:02:28.953
A woman is like poison…

01:02:34.542 --> 01:02:37.211
Cha Se-gye, Cha Se-gye! Have you lost your mind? Cha Se-gye! Open your

01:02:37.295 --> 01:02:40.590
eyes, Cha Se-gye! Cha Se-gye!

01:02:40.673 --> 01:02:41.758
Stop! Leave him alone now.

01:02:41.841 --> 01:02:44.510
I'm going to try to reanimate him with the defibrillator. Everyone get

01:02:44.594 --> 01:02:46.471
-ready. -Cha Se-gye! Cha Se-gye! No!

01:02:46.554 --> 01:02:48.264
-Leave him alone! -Open his shirt.

01:02:48.347 --> 01:02:51.976
-Okay, give me the defibrillator? -No! Don't die, don't die, Cha Se-gye.

01:02:52.059 --> 01:02:52.894
Here it is, doctor.

01:02:52.977 --> 01:02:53.811
Ma'am, please stop!

01:02:53.895 --> 01:02:54.729
Cha Se-gye.

01:02:54.812 --> 01:02:55.646
Charging!

01:03:00.651 --> 01:03:07.241
Cha Se-gye! Don't die! Cha Se-gye, Cha Se-gye, don't die. No, don't die.

01:03:07.325 --> 01:03:09.202
-Just get off! -Everyone, clear!

01:03:09.285 --> 01:03:11.287
-No. Don't die, Cha Se-gye. No! -One,

01:03:11.370 --> 01:03:14.040
-two, three! -No…

01:03:30.014 --> 01:03:33.684
Safety and security come first and also come second. In this life, I will

01:03:33.768 --> 01:03:37.730
make sure to guard my heart from pain and live to be very old.

01:03:58.459 --> 01:04:02.338
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

01:04:04.215 --> 01:04:05.049
Here.

01:04:22.984 --> 01:04:24.902
You will become his paramour.

01:04:40.793 --> 01:04:44.922
You must also have been fond of this dog. It will be grateful to you…

01:04:48.009 --> 01:04:52.138
because… thanks to you, it will not have been too lonely here.

01:04:59.937 --> 01:05:00.897
Kang clan, Dan-sim.

01:05:03.399 --> 01:05:06.986
This flower would suit you well. It stands out most strikingly, just as

01:05:07.069 --> 01:05:07.904
you do.

01:05:15.161 --> 01:05:18.664
Do not grieve too deeply. Instead of a mutt that can't talk, you could

01:05:18.748 --> 01:05:24.921
have a true companion. Would you like me to be that for you?

01:06:17.014 --> 01:06:19.517
This time, have I really crossed into the afterlife?

01:06:19.600 --> 01:06:21.852
Could this perchance be Paradise?

01:06:22.353 --> 01:06:25.606
Very well. If I am to do this, I might as well take it all off.

01:06:26.107 --> 01:06:27.650
Change her outfit again. Change it.

01:06:27.733 --> 01:06:29.568
Tell me, is there a demon in your eyes?

01:06:29.652 --> 01:06:31.862
She is the only thing you can see right now!

01:06:32.613 --> 01:06:35.074
Why are you finding fault with every little thing today? Are you

01:06:35.157 --> 01:06:39.328
tormenting me because I refused your affection? I am so very glad to be alive.

01:06:39.412 --> 01:06:40.371
Let's drink!

01:06:40.871 --> 01:06:43.457
I think the time has come. Take care of it discreetly.

01:06:43.541 --> 01:06:45.251
Is Seo-ri still not picking up?

01:06:45.751 --> 01:06:49.296
Did you see her? Where? Where the hell is she?

